



Sir
Williamsburg Septr 1st 1757



My Friend Colo. Fairfax earnestly desires his Son Wm Henry may have a Lieutts Commission in the Regiment, if any Vacancy I desire You may give him a Commission accordingly, & as You have Blank Commissions fill one up for him if any Vacancy, which will be agreeable to Sir Your mo. humble Servant1

Robt Dinwiddie

